427
428static struct ohash mchars;
429
430
431void
432mchars_free(void)
433{
434
435 ohash_delete(&mchars);
436}
437
438void
439mchars_alloc(void)
440{
441 size_t i;
442 unsigned int slot;
443
444 mandoc_ohash_init(&mchars, 9, offsetof(struct ln, roffcode));
445 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(lines)/sizeof(lines[0]); i++) {
446 slot = ohash_qlookup(&mchars, lines[i].roffcode);
447 assert(ohash_find(&mchars, slot) == NULL);
448 ohash_insert(&mchars, slot, lines + i);
449 }
450}
451
452int
453mchars_spec2cp(const char *p, size_t sz)
454{
455 const struct ln *ln;
456 const char *end;
457
458 end = p + sz;
459 ln = ohash_find(&mchars, ohash_qlookupi(&mchars, p, &end));
460 return ln != NULL ? ln->unicode : -1;
461}
462
463int
464mchars_num2char(const char *p, size_t sz)
465{
466 int i;
467
468 i = mandoc_strntoi(p, sz, 10);
469 return i >= 0 && i < 256 ? i : -1;
470}
471
472int
473mchars_num2uc(const char *p, size_t sz)
474{
475 int i;
476
477 i = mandoc_strntoi(p, sz, 16);
478 assert(i >= 0 && i <= 0x10FFFF);
479 return i;
480}
481
482const char *
483mchars_spec2str(const char *p, size_t sz, size_t *rsz)
484{
485 const struct ln *ln;
486 const char *end;
487
488 end = p + sz;
489 ln = ohash_find(&mchars, ohash_qlookupi(&mchars, p, &end));
490 if (ln == NULL)
491 return NULL;
492
493 *rsz = strlen(ln->ascii);
494 return ln->ascii;
495}
496
497const char *
498mchars_uc2str(int uc)
499{
500 size_t i;
501
502 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(lines)/sizeof(lines[0]); i++)
503 if (uc == lines[i].unicode)
504 return lines[i].ascii;
505 return "<?>";
506}
